ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Great course. Challenging and need to stay on top of the readings and notes, and give yourself sufficient time to study for exams. Will learn a lot.
Lots of good info to be learned
Weekly homeworks with and emphasis on concept learning overall. Strong chemistry knowledge a big help

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Definitely helped me understand underlying concepts very significant to my interests in nutrition and medicine. I could have done without all the evolutionary assumptions, given that's only one narrative of creation that I don't agree with, nor do I think actually attests to the beautify and intricacy that biochemistry reveals. But alas, it takes eyes to see that. Certainly encouraged me to continue learning more about biochemistry.
